xwikidoc.content: <vijay13> has quit 08:56 <vijay13> has quit 12:40 <SayAsh> has joined #phenotips 13:02 <akats> has joined #phenotips 13:12 <akats> before I forget, the worlds biggest bookstore is going out of business. 50% off everything. 13:13 <sdumitriu_[Away]> The one two minutes away from here? 13:13 <sdumitriu_[Away]> is now known as <sdumitriu> 13:15 <akats> yup 14:20 <SayAsh> has quit 14:20 <SayAsh_> has joined #phenotips 14:42 <SayAsh_> has quit 15:18 <shalinshah1993> has quit 15:33 <mcupak> has quit 16:28 <akats> There is kinda of a big problem with updating my patient-network code to the latest. I'm missing exomizer. 16:29 <akats> As far as I understand it's not online 16:29 <akats> as in nexus 16:29 <sdumitriu> True 16:29 <sdumitriu> That's what we're negotiating now with the authors 16:29 <sdumitriu> I'll send it by email 16:30 <akats> thanks 16:30 <akats> though, where do I put it? 16:31 <sdumitriu> Instructions included 16:31 <sdumitriu> Delivering, it's big 16:36 <akats> Sweet 16:45 <akats> Don't the jars from patient-network got into phenotips/WEB-INF/lib? 16:45 <sdumitriu> When? 16:46 <sdumitriu> They do when building phenomecentral.org, not when building phenotips 16:47 <akats> I put all the freshly built jars from patient-network into my current phenomecentral.org, but none of them gave me an overwrite warning 16:48 <akats> That's why I'm asking 16:48 <sdumitriu> What overwrite warning? 16:48 <sdumitriu> There shouldn't be an overwrite warning 16:48 <sdumitriu> Or do you mean the cp confirmation? 16:49 <sdumitriu> You might have encountered an issue that I'm working on right now, they might have a different name 16:49 <akats> Yup, I should've looked before asking you. 16:49 <sdumitriu> Run this in WEB-INF/libs: ls -1 | sed -r -e s/[0-9.]+//g | uniq -d 16:50 <akats> They do have a different name. The original has the build time in it 16:51 <sdumitriu> Yes 16:51 <sdumitriu> Remove those 16:51 <akats> Thanks 18:57 <akats> has quit
